          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two small CH(2) targets, 10*10*2.3-mm**3 and",
                " 10*10*1.5-mm**3, were used for data taking while two",
                "corresponding C-targets, 10*10*1-mm**3 and 10*10*0.5-",
                "mm*3, were used to find the background contribution.",
                "The thinner targets used for the three most forward",
                "angles were oriented at an angle of +35-degree with",
                "respect to the beam direction to reduce the energy loss",
                "of the recoil protons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors. Test without the target showed that the",
                "air surrounding it contributes to the background. Test",
                "with a large He-gas target replacing air showed only",
                "accidentals. Therefore the fact that was chose C-target",
                "with C amounts equivalent to those of the CH(2) targets",
                "accounts correctly for the air contribution."
              ]
            }
          ],
